summary: This document is a financial statement from Deutsche Bank detailing account transactions for a specific account. It includes information on deposits, withdrawals, and account balances for the month of November 2016, highlighting significant outgoing transfers and interest payments.
keyFacts: The account had a beginning balance of $43,733,129.26 on November 1, 2016.
A total of $24,784,000.00 was debited from the account during November 2016.
An interest payment of $5,807.67 was credited to the account on November 30, 2016.
Significant outgoing transfers included $1,500,000.00 to Silicon Valley Bank and $23,000,000.00 to an unspecified account.
The ending balance of the account as of November 30, 2016, was $18,954,936.93.
